s
\Re(s) > 1
 \sum_{n=1}^\infty \int_0^\infty \left|e^{-nx} x^{s-1} \right| dx =  \sum_{n=1}^\infty \int_0^\infty e^{-nx} x^{\left| s-1 \right|} dx 
 \sum_{n=1}^\infty \int_0^\infty \left|e^{-nx} x^{s-1} \right| dx \le \sum_{n=1}^\infty \int_0^\infty e^{-nx} x^{\left| s-1 \right|} dx 
x
s=\sigma+it
\sigma,t\in\mathbb R
x^{s-1}=x^{\sigma-1}\cdot x^{it}
x^{it}=e^{it\ln x}
1
\left |x^{s-1}\right|=x^{\sigma-1}
